## Code Guidelines And Resources

When we look at code, we'll judge it according to a few general factors:

- **Is it bug-free and working as it should across all major browsers and devices?** See  [Browser And Device Support](#browser-and-device-support) at the bottom of this page for the full list of browsers and devices we'll test on. We recommend [Saucelabs](https://saucelabs.com/) or a similar tool for testing.

- **Is the code organized, readable, modular, maintainable, and extendable?** This includes organization of directories, files, and components, keeping files **short**, clean separation of html, css, and javascript, **naming things well**, consistent indentation, and following best practices for each language.

- **Does it rely on solid libraries and components?** When open source libraries and components are used, we will be checking on them to ensure they are architecturally sound, well-documented, and have developer-friendly APIs.

Rather than dig any further into the details of a topic that could fill several books (or several libraries), we'll point you toward a few style guides that we think offer good advice on keeping front-end code well structured. We aren't requiring that submissions follow *every* rule in these guides. We understand that people have their own styles. We don't need uniformity, but we *do* need fanatical devotion to organization, readability, and quality.

- [Codeguide.co](http://codeguide.co/){:target="_blank"} - a good all around front-end guide.

- [Github's CSS Style Guide](https://github.com/styleguide/css){:target="_blank"} - well-written and fairly brief guide to good css.

- [Google's HTML and CSS Style Guide](https://google-styleguide.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/htmlcssguide.xml#Semantics){:target="_blank"} - comprehensive with lots of examples.

- [Airbnb's JavaScript Style Guide](https://github.com/airbnb/javascript){:target="_blank"} - a quite thorough guide to writing clean and robust javascript.

- [JQuery JavaScript Style Guide](http://contribute.jquery.org/style-guide/js/){:target="_blank"} and [JQuery HTML Style Guide](http://contribute.jquery.org/style-guide/html/){:target="_blank"} - a JQuery-oriented perspective.

- [CoffeeScript Style Guide](https://github.com/polarmobile/coffeescript-style-guide){:target="_blank"} - a good collection of best practices if you use CoffeeScript in your template.

- [ZURB Responsive Design Best Practices](http://zurb.com/responsive/design){:target="_blank"} - a guide from the creators of the responsive Foundation framework.

- [A List Apart Responsive Design Overview](http://alistapart.com/article/responsive-web-design){:target="_blank"} - a very well-written overview of the key considerations for designing and building responsive sites.

- [Wordpress Best Practices](http://vip.wordpress.com/documentation/best-practices/){:target="_blank"} - best practices for Wordpress plugins and themes.

- [Magento Best Practices](http://www.sitepoint.com/magento-basics-request-flow-standards-best-practices/){:target="_blank"} - Sitepoint article on Magento best practices.
